claim.claim-text:
21. A freight information management method in a freight information management system, comprising: 
on the basis of a consignor address and a consignee address of freight requested to be delivered from a consignor destination, determining a delivery route of said freight in a freight information management center; 
writing the thus determined delivery route into an electronic tag attached to said freight remotely from said freight information center; 
while said freight is delivered via a plurality of collection/delivery stations in accordance with the delivery route in the electronic tag attached to said freight, determining a redelivery route of said freight in response to a change of said consignee address in the freight information management center; 
writing the thus determined redelivery route into said electronic tag attached to said freight remotely from said freight information center; and 
changing the delivery route of said freight in accordance with the redelivery route in said electronic tag attached to said freight.

23. A freight information management method in a freight information management system, comprising: 
in a freight information management center, determining a delivery schedule of freight on the basis of consignor information and consignee information of said freight requested to be delivered at a consignor destination; 
writing the thus determined delivery schedule into an electronic tag attached to said freight remotely from said freight information center; 
while said freight is delivered via a plurality of collection/delivery stations in accordance with the delivery schedule in the electronic tag attached to said freight, comparing an actual delivery condition of said freight with said delivery schedule read out of said electronic tag attached to said freight in each collection/delivery station; and 
delivering an alarm informing that an irregular delivery schedule occurs in that collection/delivery station when a result of said comparison is non-coincident.

29. A storage medium used in a freight information management system and readable by a computer, comprising: 
a process portion for determining a delivery route of freight in a freight information management center on the basis of a consignor address and a consignee address of said freight requested to be delivered from a consignor destination; 
a process portion for writing the thus determined delivery route into an electronic tag attached to said freight remotely from said freight information center; 
a process portion for determining, while said freight is delivered via a plurality of collection/delivery stations in accordance with the delivery route in the electronic tag attached to said freight, a redelivery route of said freight in the freight information management center in response to a change of said consignee address; and 
a process portion for writing the thus determined redelivery route into said electronic tag attached to said freight remotely from said freight information center to change the delivery route of said freight in accordance with the redelivery route in said electronic tag attached to said freight.
